							<!-- End each blog post -->
							
														
							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/monicamacansantos/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Screen-Shot-2022-10-07-at-10.08.58-AM-100x100.png" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Screen-Shot-2022-10-07-at-10.08.58-AM-300x300.png 2x" alt="Monica Macansantos" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/monicamacansantos/">Monica Macansantos</a></h6>
										Monica Macansantos is the author of the essay collection <em>Returning to My Father’s Kitchen</em> (Curbstone, 2025) and the story collection <em>Love and Other Rituals</em> (2022). She was recently a Shearing Fellow with the Black Mountain Institute in Las Vegas and is a graduate of the Michener Center for Writers. Her writing has recently appeared in <em>River Styx</em>, <em>Bennington Review</em>, and <em>Poor Yorick</em>.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
							<br class="clear"/>
						</div>
